constructor.details: Establishes the initial owner and the base URI for metadata.

params.initialOwner: The address assigned as the initial owner of the contract.

exists(uint256).details: Indicates whether any token exist with a given id, or not.

mint(address,uint256,uint256,bytes).details: Creates a certain number of tokens with a designated ID for a specific address. Only callable by the contract owner.

params.amount: The number of tokens to mint.
params.data: Additional data that goes along with the minting process.
params.id: The unique ID of the token to be minted.
params.to: The address receiving the newly minted tokens.

mintBatch(address,uint256[],uint256[],by.details: Creates a batch of tokens for specified IDs and assigns them to a specific address. Executable only by the contract owner.

params.amounts: An array specifying the number of tokens to mint for each ID.
params.data: Additional data that is included with the minting.
params.ids: An array of unique token IDs to be minted.
params.to: The recipient address for the newly minted batch of tokens.

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby disabling any functionality that is only available to the owner.

totalSupply(uint256).details: Total value of tokens in with a given id.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

uri(uint256).details: Generates the full URI by concatenating the base URI and the string representation of the token ID.

params.id: The unique token ID of interest.

returns._0: A string representing the complete metadata URI for the specified token.

constructor.notice: Initializes the contract with the base URI for all token types and sets the initial owner.

mint(address,uint256,uint256,bytes).notice: Mint a new set of tokens with specific metadata.

mintBatch(address,uint256[],uint256[],by.notice: Mint a batch of multiple tokens at once.
